      • addMappingsFromFile

        public static boolean addMappingsFromFile(java.lang.String path,
                                          java.lang.Class sourceClass)
                                   throws java.io.IOException,
                                          java.lang.IllegalStateException,
                                          SDL_Error
        This method adds mappings held in the specified file. The file is copied to the temp folder so that it can be read by the native code (if running from a .jar for instance)
        Parameters:
        path - The path to the file containing controller mappings.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if the file cannot be read, copied to a temp folder, or deleted.
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - if the mappings cannot be applied to SDL
        SDL_Error
